rComments: Her tests are ridiculous: LA/SA AND an essay in 2hrs. A portion of the class simply do not finish writing in time. Course critique aside, she is a nice person and does her best to make the material interesting.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Great prof took her intro to psych class at gbc super easy tests

Overall a passionate and inspiring prof, and the course material in itself is not hard. HOWEVER, her rigorous guidelines and convoluted marking breakdown make this course on emotions far more 'emotional' than it should be.

Nice prof. but she provides very little guidance when it comes to her examinations - not to mention they are all short answer/essay. Slides do not make sense on their own and she does not even post the course readings on blackboard. Despite that she is kind, she still goes out of her way to make the course more difficult than it should be.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Dr. Luby is a wonderful person and very easy to approach, however, the workload for this course is HIGH and the material is BORING. Attending lectures is a MUST and make sure you take good notes because her slides are VAGUE. Additionally, the research paper due at the end is complicated and they mark you pretty tough!

She took over from our previous professor who got a bug at the starting of our semester. Considering the fact that we missed two lectures, she did an amazing job by covering all the required curriculum. Not once did she rush the lectures and made it look like she was only teaching for the sake of covering the entire syllabus. She is FUNNY! :)
I took her introduction to psychology course at George brown college, she's a fantastic professor and an overall nice person. I would love to take the course again.
she was nice and pleasant enough to listen to and she gave decent opportunities to boost marks but her evaluations were more stressful than they had to be for the material. Would not take again.
Great prof overall. Very organized and concise. Tests are fair.
Great prof. Thoroughly enjoyed her class. Study the assigned readings well (they are all journal articles), and quizzes tend to be specific but fair.

Decent lecturer, but great all-around person. Easy to talk to and willing to explain concepts thoroughly if you don't understand them. She's always happy to have students visit her. Found that reviewing her lecture notes is enough to do well on the tests.

Average professor, she reads off the slides most of the time making the class really boring. Midterm was long and tough, marking was terrible as well. First professor in my three years of university to immediately reject my request for a remark without any reason. To future students, her marking is extremely harsh on the research paper so be ready

She's a sweet lecturer and really wants her students to improve. However, her slides were exactly the same info as the textbook (less detailed), making the material get very dull. BUT she does only test on main big studies/models she discusses in detail. She's also very approachable, I never spoke once in class and still got participation marks.

I think she is one of the most inspiring, thought-provoking, approachable professors at UofT. I sincerely felt bad when I had to miss out on her lectures. This course was very interesting and often motivated me to seek more positivity in life. The only thing I didn't like was that the lectures were 3 hours long, but I still recommend it to anyone.

Fantastic for stats. The assignment is my only complaint, the instructions were not very clear and she refuses to explain them to the class, but her exams are easy, so I still ended up with an A, though she made the final exam much longer (3 hours, barely anyone finished) and complicated than the midterm because the class had such a high average

Dr. Luby is an all-around great prof. She makes classes interactive, is a fair-to-easy test writer, and will bend over backwards to help you during her office hours. I liked her so much I'm taking 2 more of her classes this semester. Also: she's funny and a real person, not a stuffed shirt.

She's really nice and always willing to explain concepts. The course material was quite dry, and there wasn't much she could do to make it interesting. She'll try to scare you by not giving many details about the test, but it ends up being easy and only testing main concepts. Text book use is almost 0. Overall an easy but boring class
I don't know what it is about her, but I think she's really sexy. Very smart, articulate and seems really sweet too.

Dr. Luby is a great professor! She has the most awkwardly funny attitude, but always makes sure we understand concepts. The final assignment was not easy, but it was good that she didn't baby us for it. We had to learn to make our own decisions. Great prof for stats, made it very entertaining! Slides are easy to learn from.
Great teacher

She is the best teacher I have ever had. Her tests are extremely straightforward and easy but she's kinda a funny teacher in her own little way. If you want a 4.0 then take her classes cause she is not a hard test maker!

The definition of the word incompetent. She constantly makes computational errors on her own slides. She is easily confused, and unclear. She spent almost 3 hours talking about mean, median and mode, and spent less than an hour on more important statistical tests. Assignment ambiguous assignments without ever discussing them in class.
